{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}} {{Use Australian English|date=November 2016}} The '''Colonial Secretary of Van Diemen's Land''' (later '''Colonial Secretary of Tasmania''') was the representative of the [[Great Britain|British]] [[Colonial Office]] in [[Van Diemen's Land]] (later [[Tasmania]]), and was usually appointed from Britain. In 1884, the role was renamed Chief Secretary.
==List of Colonial Secretaries of Van Diemen's Land/Tasmania==
The following is an incomplete list of Colonial Secretaries of Van Diemen's Land/Tasmania:
