AAAMAAJ|year=2000|publisher=Crown Publ.}}</ref> |- | [[Cherokee Park]] || [[Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville]] || [[Kentucky]] || |- | [[Canfield Casino and Congress Park|Congress Park]] || [[Saratoga Springs, New York|Saratoga Springs]] || New York || |- | [[Cushing Island, Maine|Cushing Island]] || || [[Maine]] || |- | [[D.W. Field Park]] || [[Brockton, Massachusetts|Brockton]] || Massachusetts || |- | [[Downing Park (Newburgh, New York)|Downing Park]] || [[Newburgh (city), New York|Newburgh]] || New York || |- | [[Druid Hills, Georgia|Druid Hills]] || || [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] || |- | [[Eastern Parkway (Brooklyn)|Eastern Parkway]] || [[Brooklyn]] || New York<ref name="AIA"/> || |- | [[Edgewood Park Historic District|Edgewood Park]] || [[Westville, New Haven]] || [[Connecticut]] || |- | [[Elizabeth Park (Connecticut)|Elizabeth Park]] || [[Hartford, Connecticut|Hartford]] & [[West Hartford, Connecticut|West Hartford]] || [[Connecticut]] || |- | [[Elmwood Cemetery (Detroit, Michigan)|Elmwood Cemetery]] || [[Detroit]] || [[Michigan]] || |- | [[Emerald Necklace]] || [[Boston]] || [[Massachusetts]] || |- | Filmore Farm [[Charles Henry Jones (businessman)|Charles Henry Jones]] || || || circa 1880 |- | [[Wade Park District|Fine Arts Garden]] || [[Cleveland]] || [[Ohio]]<ref name="CMA">[http://www.clevelandart.org/research/in-the-library/collection-in-focus/fine-arts-garden|The Fine Arts Garden]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Cleveland Museum of Art, accessed 2014-05-11.</ref> || |- | Florham, former estate of Hamilton and Florence (Vanderbilt) Twombly. Now the campus of [[Fairleigh Dickinson University]] || [[Florham Park, New Jersey|Florham Park]] || [[New Jersey]] || |- | [[Forest Park (Springfield)|Forest Park]] || [[Springfield, Massachusetts|Springfield]] || Massachusetts || designed in 1893 |- | [[Forest Park (Queens, New York)|Forest Park]] || [[Queens]] || New York<ref name="AIA"/> || |- | [[Fort Greene Park]] 