{{unreferenced|date=June 2018}}
In [[surveying]], a '''pole''' is bar made of wood or metal and normally held vertical, upon which different instruments can be mounted: a [[prism (surveying)|prism]], a [[GPS device]], etc. It may be manufactured with a predetermined length (e.g., 2 meters) or may be graduated for different heights or stages.
== See also == * [[Leveling staff]] * [[Surveying rod]]
[[Category:Surveying instruments]]
